    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-26T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="766"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d766">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">361.11/3767: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Reval</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Albrecht</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reval</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-26T17:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Message in your July 25, 3 p.m., delivered today to Stark who is in charge of
                    Soviet mission during Litvinov’s absence in Moscow. Stark said he would
                    telegraph it immediately to Tchitcherin and deliver to me the reply thereto as
                    soon as received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Albrecht</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
